<subSubSection id="2DF0ACA1FFE6FFD9FF71FCCCFD89FC66" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="description">
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FCCCFDD0FC97" blockId="14.[151,1436,762,968]" box="[151,557,798,825]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FF79FCCCFF14FC96" box="[159,233,798,824]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[224,1364,194,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-19@59.[214,1373,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neotropical Eudocima, Tetrisia, and Graphigona adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605510/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Figs 6</figureCitation>
: E–F, 18: C, 23: F–G, 30: D)
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6555FF2AFFE6FFD9FF71FC90FD89FC66" blockId="14.[151,1436,762,968]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
The separation of this species from 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FDC7FC91FD77FCF2" baseAuthorityName="Cramer" baseAuthorityYear="1777" box="[545,650,835,860]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="procus">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FDC7FC91FD77FCF2" box="[545,650,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. procus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FD59FC91FC99FCF2" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[703,868,834,860]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FD59FC91FC99FCF2" box="[703,868,834,860]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. serpentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is described above. It has been collected from 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FA8FFC91FA61FCF3" box="[1385,1436,835,861]" name="Peru" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Peru</collectingCountry>
through Columbia, 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FE94FCB5FE36FC2F" box="[370,459,871,897]" name="Panama" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FDE4FCB4FD7DFC2E" box="[514,640,870,896]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
. We doubt the accuracy of a 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FC22FCB4FBC1FC2E" box="[964,1084,870,896]" name="Zimbabwe" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Zimbabwe</collectingCountry>
label for 
<specimenCount id="73EC34A3FFE6FFD9FB4FFCB5FABFFC2E" box="[1193,1346,870,897]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
(
<figureCitation id="FDD1E3AFFFE6FFD9FAB4FCB4FA6AFC2E" box="[1362,1431,870,896]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="59.[151,250,1976,2000]" captionTargetBox="[224,1364,194,1945]" captionTargetId="figure-19@59.[214,1373,181,1952]" captionTargetPageId="59" captionText="FIGURE 6. Neotropical Eudocima, Tetrisia, and Graphigona adults (dorsal aspect)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6605510" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6605510/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
: E) which was obtained from a third party. Like 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FD44FC59FCBAFC0A" baseAuthorityName="Walker" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[674,839,906,932]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Eudocima" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="serpentifera">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FD44FC59FCBAFC0A" box="[674,839,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">E. serpentifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it feeds on 
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FC20FC58FB3BFC0A" box="[966,1222,906,932]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" genus="Disciphania" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calocarpa">
<emphasis id="579E2338FFE6FFD9FC20FC58FB3BFC0A" box="[966,1222,906,932]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Disciphania calocarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="A2EA84A9FFE6FFD9FB35FC58FA68FC0B" baseAuthorityName="Zaspel" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[1235,1429,906,933]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Menispermaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Menispermaceae</taxonomicName>
) in 
<collectingCountry id="1DFDBFBAFFE6FFD9FF52FC7CFED3FC66" box="[180,302,942,968]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="017B82DBFFE6FFD9FEDBFC7CFD94FC66" author="Janzen, D. H. &amp; Hallwachs, W." box="[317,617,942,968]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" refId="ref38340" refString="Janzen, D. H. &amp; Hallwachs, W. (2009) Dynamic database for an inventory of the macrocaterpillar fauna, and its food plants and parasitoides, of Area de Conservacion Guanacaste (ACG), northwestern Costa Rica (nn-SRNP-nnnnn voucher codes). Available from: http: // janzen. sas. upenn. edu (accessed 3 August 2021)" type="url" year="2009">Janzen &amp; Hallwachs 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
